      "description": "Presenting a museum-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) in Carbon Black Metallic. This specimen features the legendary S54 3.2L naturally aspirated inline-six, delivering linear power through six individual throttle bodies and a high-revving 8,000 RPM redline. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise 6-speed Getrag manual transmission and a factory-spec variable M-differential lock. This vehicle boasts a documented service history, including proactive double-VANOS maintenance and a structurally reinforced rear subframe. The suspension retains its original kinematic integrity, offering the communicative feedback expected of a flagship M-chassis. Preserved in its factory configuration with flawless paint and a pristine interior, this E46 represents the zenith of analog performance engineering.",
